1
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:16,683
2 OH KYUNG-SOOK

2
00:00:16,766 --> 00:00:19,060
The workers' friend, Oh Kyung-sook

3
00:00:19,602 --> 00:00:22,439
Friend to women, Oh Kyung-sook

4
00:00:23,148 --> 00:00:24,774
A better world to live in together…

5
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:27,569
Dear fellow citizens of Seoul,
this is Oh Kyung-sook.

6
00:00:28,987 --> 00:00:32,032
New Seoul, new politics!

7
00:00:32,115 --> 00:00:35,702
I, the new face, Oh Kyung-sook,
will make politics

8
00:00:35,785 --> 00:00:40,040
serve the common people
and make Seoul a city for our children!

9
00:00:40,123 --> 00:00:41,332
Oh Kyung-sook!

10
00:00:47,756 --> 00:00:49,132
You can trust Oh Kyung-sook

11
00:00:49,215 --> 00:00:51,760
Candidate Number two, Oh Kyung-sook!

12
00:00:52,761 --> 00:00:57,932
Yes. I also have a son around your age.

13
00:00:58,016 --> 00:01:01,311
I promised my son one thing.

14
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:04,564
That he would have a happy adulthood

15
00:01:04,647 --> 00:01:07,817
in a better world built by his mother.

16
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:12,238
Dear teens, our future voters,
I love you all!

17
00:01:13,865 --> 00:01:16,159
Have a great day!

18
00:01:16,993 --> 00:01:18,411
-Hey! You'll kill him.
-Stop!

19
00:01:33,843 --> 00:01:38,306
-Oh Kyung-sook!
-Oh Kyung-sook!

20
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:22,016
Look, do you have a grudge against my son?

21
00:02:22,559 --> 00:02:23,560
Have you seen him?

22
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:26,479
Hyun-woo.

23
00:02:33,903 --> 00:02:34,821
Oh my gosh.

24
00:02:38,158 --> 00:02:38,992
Oh gosh.

25
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:41,077
You must be quite shocked.

26
00:02:41,786 --> 00:02:43,705
Let's find out what happened exactly--

27
00:02:43,788 --> 00:02:44,956
Isn't it obvious?

28
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:48,501
Oh Kyung-sook. Is your son a thug?

29
00:02:49,752 --> 00:02:52,213
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry, I really am.

30
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:53,631
What good is your apology?

31
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:56,050
You should educate your son

32
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:58,970
instead of gallivanting around,
playing politician.

33
00:02:59,053 --> 00:03:02,432
Why not try being a decent parent
before meddling in politics?

34
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,520
How did this happen?

35
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:10,273
He beat me up. It was one-sided.

36
00:03:12,442 --> 00:03:13,818
One-sided?

37
00:03:13,902 --> 00:03:18,656
I didn't do anything, but Kang Hyun-woo
went nuts and started beating me up.

38
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,533
Do you see?

39
00:03:20,617 --> 00:03:25,079
Oh Kyung-sook, your son beat up my child
on the street for no reason.

40
00:03:25,163 --> 00:03:27,498
My son's so shocked that he doesn't think

41
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:29,959
he can go outside or go to school anymore.

42
00:03:31,669 --> 00:03:32,503
Hyun-woo.

43
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:35,381
Tell me. Is all of this true?

44
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:37,717
Why won't you say anything?

45
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:41,804
How could you do such a thing?

46
00:03:43,264 --> 00:03:45,350
Why? Are you scared?

47
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:47,435
That you'll lose the election
because of me?

48
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:49,103
Hey, Hyun-woo.

49
00:03:49,187 --> 00:03:50,438
Hyun-woo.

50
00:03:50,521 --> 00:03:51,773
Are you even worried about me?

51
00:03:52,732 --> 00:03:55,568
You came because you're afraid
I might ruin the election!

52
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,529
You could be mayor if it weren't for me,

53
00:03:58,613 --> 00:03:59,948
but I'm getting in your way.

54
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:02,575
How? How could you say such a thing?

55
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:05,828
How could you?
Is that how I taught you? Huh?

56
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:07,747
When did you ever teach me anything?

57
00:04:08,289 --> 00:04:09,999
Tell me one thing you taught me.

58
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:12,460
Hey, Hyun-woo. Watch your tone.

59
00:04:12,961 --> 00:04:14,128
Let's stop there.

60
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:19,384
I think Gyeong-min
should be taken to a hospital first.

61
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:22,595
We'll drive you to the hospital,
so tell us if you need anything--

62
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:25,932
Why? So you can settle
and make this go away with money?

63
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:27,600
Ma'am.

64
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:30,561
Are you trying to buy our silence
so he won't go to jail?

65
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:32,355
No, that's not it.

66
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:36,401
We don't have the slightest intention
of settling, so don't even dream of it.

67
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:42,365
We're done being questioned,
so we're leaving. Okay?

68
00:04:43,616 --> 00:04:44,450
Let's go.

69
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:45,785
I'm sorry.

70
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:47,328
I'm so sorry.

71
00:04:48,037 --> 00:04:49,372
Here. Take a seat.

72
00:04:53,876 --> 00:04:55,128
This is all my fault.

73
00:04:58,172 --> 00:04:59,757
How did I let that happen to him?

74
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:02,176
Don't say that. It's not your fault.

75
00:05:02,719 --> 00:05:05,013
Has Hyun-woo had problems
at school before?

76
00:05:06,097 --> 00:05:07,265
It doesn't make sense

77
00:05:08,516 --> 00:05:10,893
that he'd beat him for no reason.

78
00:05:11,936 --> 00:05:14,772
Well, I did notice something strange
a few days ago.

79
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:19,944
He had blood on his uniform.

80
00:05:20,945 --> 00:05:23,197
I was startled.
I asked him what had happened.

81
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:26,409
He told me that he'd gotten
into a scuffle with his friends.

82
00:05:28,911 --> 00:05:32,790
Honey. You should have told me then.

83
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:35,293
Why didn't you tell me, huh?

84
00:05:35,376 --> 00:05:38,921
You're so busy with your campaign
that you don't even have time to eat.

85
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:41,007
When and how was I supposed to tell you?

86
00:05:43,885 --> 00:05:44,719
Kyung-sook.

87
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:47,096
I know it's hard, but be strong.

88
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:50,433
I know this is hard as a mother,

89
00:05:51,976 --> 00:05:54,270
but it might hurt you
on the political front too.

90
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:02,820
I'll settle with the parents
as quickly as I can,

91
00:06:02,904 --> 00:06:04,072
so look after Hyun-woo.

92
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:06,616
And keep me updated on the investigation.

93
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:10,244
I'm sorry. You're busy enough already
without our son causing trouble.

94
00:06:10,328 --> 00:06:11,579
We'll have to determine

95
00:06:12,455 --> 00:06:13,831
whether he started this

96
00:06:14,457 --> 00:06:16,334
or was unwittingly dragged into it.

97
00:06:16,417 --> 00:06:18,586
Then I'll talk to Hyun-woo's
school friends

98
00:06:18,669 --> 00:06:21,547
and find out exactly how this fight began.

99
00:06:22,715 --> 00:06:24,050
Make sure it doesn't leak.

100
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:25,385
Especially

101
00:06:26,511 --> 00:06:28,346
to Baek Jae-min's camp.

102
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:30,056
Never.

103
00:06:32,016 --> 00:06:34,769
Wow, what a good boy!

104
00:06:36,145 --> 00:06:37,814
Like mother, like son.

105
00:06:37,897 --> 00:06:39,816
He charged headfirst into trouble.

106
00:06:40,316 --> 00:06:42,860
We should start leading
the bull to its demise.

107
00:06:42,944 --> 00:06:43,820
Ms. Guk.

108
00:06:51,285 --> 00:06:54,038
In two days,
the blackout period will begin.

109
00:06:54,705 --> 00:06:57,750
That's when official opinion polls
are no longer released

110
00:06:57,834 --> 00:07:01,295
and most swing and shy voters
shift their support.

111
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:04,257
It also means if Oh Kyung-sook
is still in the race by then,

112
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:07,510
there's no telling how many of my votes
she'll chew through.

113
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:09,011
She'll pull out before then.

114
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:14,600
We'll smear her image
beyond the point of no return.

115
00:07:14,684 --> 00:07:17,562
But she might dig her heels in
and refuse to withdraw.

116
00:07:17,645 --> 00:07:19,564
That won't hurt us. All she'd do

117
00:07:20,314 --> 00:07:23,818
is humiliate herself
for the remainder of the campaign.

118
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:25,695
Has there ever been

119
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:30,074
a politician elected after a controversy
about their family surfaced?

120
00:07:30,158 --> 00:07:30,992
There hasn't.

121
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:36,289
And family issues can be fatal
for female politicians.

122
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,710
Whether she withdraws or decides to fight,

123
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:44,589
all that's left for us to do
is to sit back and watch

124
00:07:45,506 --> 00:07:47,717
how Oh Kyung-sook falls.

125
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:50,803
-Ms. Guk, proceed.
-Yes, sir.

126
00:07:53,389 --> 00:07:54,432
A rat in a trap.

127
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:58,561
It's been reported that the bully
assaulting a fellow student

128
00:07:58,644 --> 00:08:00,980
in the video that surfaced online today

129
00:08:01,063 --> 00:08:04,567
is actually the son of Oh Kyung-sook,
Reform Party of Korea's candidate,

130
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:05,860
shocking the public.

131
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:08,029
The victim was seriously injured

132
00:08:08,112 --> 00:08:10,281
and is receiving treatment at a hospital.

133
00:08:10,364 --> 00:08:12,241
He's experiencing severe mental trauma

134
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:15,495
that will require therapy.

135
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:18,581
Candidate Oh, loved for her righteous
and down-to-earth image,

136
00:08:18,664 --> 00:08:22,293
was a strong candidate for the election,

137
00:08:22,376 --> 00:08:25,671
but voters' anger and disappointment
are now on the rise.

138
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:27,798
It's too early to consider

139
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:29,842
her withdrawal.

140
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:32,261
The party is also looking into it.

141
00:08:33,221 --> 00:08:35,223
We'll get to the bottom of this incident

142
00:08:35,806 --> 00:08:39,101
and hold an official press conference,
so please be patient.

143
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:43,940
Oh, and please refrain from publishing
any speculative articles.

144
00:08:47,985 --> 00:08:49,820
Call the camp and ask what happened!

145
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:50,947
Any comments for us?

146
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:51,864
Mr. Yang!

147
00:08:51,948 --> 00:08:52,949
BEAT CLASSMATE MERCILESSLY

148
00:08:53,032 --> 00:08:54,408
"Powergate"?

149
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:57,787
You've got to be kidding me.

150
00:08:58,329 --> 00:09:01,165
This is just distorting the truth
beyond all plausibility!

151
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:02,959
They're trying to frame this issue,

152
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:07,338
deliberately using the word "power"
to make Ms. Oh look bad.

153
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:11,133
Ms. Hwang. Why don't we warn the press?

154
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:14,136
To stop posting clickbait news
on an ongoing investigation.

155
00:09:16,514 --> 00:09:18,516
That's not the main issue here.

156
00:09:20,851 --> 00:09:23,479
It's strange how this story is spreading.

157
00:09:24,188 --> 00:09:26,691
This fight occurred spontaneously,

158
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:32,196
yet the footage was filmed meticulously
to show Hyun-woo's face.

159
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:35,366
The police showed up right away,
as if they were waiting.

160
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:39,620
And the footage went viral
abnormally fast.

161
00:09:39,704 --> 00:09:40,913
It all fits too…

162
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:42,957
Too well to be a coincidence, right?

163
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:48,588
As soon as the footage spread,

164
00:09:48,671 --> 00:09:52,091
media outlets favoring Baek Jae-min
began churning out articles.

165
00:09:52,174 --> 00:09:55,678
They're trying to frame Ms. Oh
and smear her image to the voters

166
00:09:55,761 --> 00:09:58,180
by making it seem like
her son's abusing her power.

167
00:09:59,807 --> 00:10:02,685
This is the most popular tactic
during the blackout period.

168
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:07,315
They're using provocative black propaganda
to lure the swing voters

169
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,233
in a final volley.

170
00:10:13,904 --> 00:10:14,739
So…

171
00:10:16,991 --> 00:10:17,825
Hyun-woo was…

172
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:21,078
It's likely he was set up.

173
00:10:21,662 --> 00:10:22,538
Highly likely.

174
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:29,879
IBC REPORTER KIM CHO-RONG

175
00:10:29,962 --> 00:10:33,299
PRESS CONFERENCE
CANDIDATE OH'S SON'S VIOLENCE

176
00:10:33,382 --> 00:10:36,969
PUNISH THE AGGRESSIVE JUVENILE OFFENDER
HIDING BEHIND THE LAW'S PROTECTION

177
00:10:38,095 --> 00:10:40,556
We will now begin
the press conference addressing

178
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:43,100
Candidate Oh's son's assault
on another student.

179
00:10:49,857 --> 00:10:53,611
Candidate Oh Kyung-sook's son
beat up our son mercilessly.

180
00:10:55,404 --> 00:10:57,531
The police treated my son as the assailant

181
00:10:58,157 --> 00:11:01,243
and only seemed to care
about protecting Candidate Oh's son.

182
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:05,247
I begged them to at least let us
take him to the hospital, but…

183
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:10,628
Both the police and Candidate Oh

184
00:11:12,129 --> 00:11:14,507
have been coercing us
into settling with them.

185
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:17,718
For our son, who fell victim
to this horrible school violence…

186
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:19,595
Ms. Hwang.

187
00:11:21,138 --> 00:11:22,765
Are we just going to do nothing?

188
00:11:23,849 --> 00:11:27,561
Shouldn't we also be publishing articles
and setting the record straight?

189
00:11:28,813 --> 00:11:29,730
Ms. Hwang.

190
00:11:30,564 --> 00:11:31,399
Look at this.

191
00:11:32,149 --> 00:11:34,902
POLICE WORRIED ABOUT CANDIDATE OH

192
00:11:34,985 --> 00:11:37,738
THE PROTECTORS OF THE PEOPLE
BECAME THE RHINO'S SHIELD

193
00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:42,785
What's going on here?
Why is the press targeting us?

194
00:11:43,577 --> 00:11:45,079
We're utterly bewildered as well.

195
00:11:45,162 --> 00:11:48,124
The officers arrested him,
not knowing he was Oh Kyung-sook's son,

196
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:51,001
and they had only just begun
writing the report…

197
00:11:51,085 --> 00:11:52,670
-Sir.
-What now?

198
00:11:52,753 --> 00:11:54,004
There's a new article.

199
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:57,717
"Oh asked Commissioner General
Heo Cheol-gyun to cover up her son's case

200
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,678
as a favor by offering him
a free pass at the hearing."

201
00:12:00,761 --> 00:12:01,595
What?

202
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:05,474
Who the hell's writing this bullshit?
Jeez.

203
00:12:13,774 --> 00:12:14,608
Hand it over?

204
00:12:15,443 --> 00:12:19,029
Our officers are doing fine. Why would
we give this case to the prosecution?

205
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:24,577
Do you think the police still
play the lackey for the prosecution?

206
00:12:24,660 --> 00:12:28,456
The more you drag this out,
the worse things will get for you.

207
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:32,251
"The four-star commissioner general

208
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:35,880
abuses his power in order to protect
Oh Kyung-sook's son."

209
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:38,632
"Dirtiest election in history,
rigged by the police."

210
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,719
"The protectors of the people
reek of corruption."

211
00:12:41,802 --> 00:12:45,514
You will be up to your neck
in disgusting headlines like those.

212
00:12:45,598 --> 00:12:47,391
I'm the commissioner general!

213
00:12:47,475 --> 00:12:50,519
Who do you think you are trying
to threaten? How dare you!

214
00:12:50,603 --> 00:12:53,147
Doesn't your term end next year?

215
00:12:55,274 --> 00:12:57,151
A minister from the police,

216
00:12:58,736 --> 00:13:01,989
that's what the police need
to grow beyond its role

217
00:13:02,072 --> 00:13:04,074
as the prosecution's lackey…

218
00:13:07,244 --> 00:13:09,705
As soon as Candidate Baek
is elected mayor,

219
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:11,665
he'll be preparing the presidential race.

220
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:14,126
The president appoints
the Interior Minister.

221
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:19,089
I believe that position is open
and could be waiting for you.

222
00:13:21,717 --> 00:13:22,551
Wait.

223
00:13:23,677 --> 00:13:24,887
The prosecution?

224
00:13:26,931 --> 00:13:29,350
They're still investigating.
Why would they be--

225
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:30,309
It's done.

226
00:13:31,018 --> 00:13:33,479
This case has been transferred
to the prosecution.

227
00:13:34,313 --> 00:13:37,733
It's a felony, and the victim
strongly wants to press charges,

228
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:39,068
so the prosecution should--

229
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:39,985
I've been

230
00:13:40,861 --> 00:13:43,739
defending juvenile offenders pro bono
for about ten years.

231
00:13:44,323 --> 00:13:46,742
I've seen many kids
who were charged unfairly

232
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:49,411
because of missteps
during police investigations.

233
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:53,165
Are you saying
your son is being accused unfairly?

234
00:13:56,252 --> 00:14:00,422
I do not deny that what my son
did was wrong. Not at all.

235
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:03,217
He should pay for his crime. Of course.

236
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:08,180
But shouldn't his investigation be fair
and transparent for that to be possible?

237
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:10,182
Ending the investigation hastily

238
00:14:10,266 --> 00:14:13,143
without telling his parents
and sending it to the prosecution…

239
00:14:13,227 --> 00:14:14,812
Sir, you're violating regulations--

240
00:14:14,895 --> 00:14:17,565
This isn't the time
to be nitpicking over regulations.

241
00:14:18,148 --> 00:14:18,983
This is

242
00:14:20,317 --> 00:14:21,861
an attempted murder case.

243
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:25,906
My gosh, attempted murder?
How could you say such a horrible thing?

244
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:29,368
Look here.

245
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:34,748
The victim was struck with a bag
filled with glass bottles.

246
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:37,668
This isn't just a common assault.

247
00:14:37,751 --> 00:14:40,212
This is a aggravated assault
with a deadly weapon.

248
00:14:40,796 --> 00:14:42,756
You're a lawyer, so you must know.

249
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:46,343
Aggravated assault cases are prosecuted
